Figure Caption: XRD patterns of Coxalloys: (a)x= 5, (b)x= 10, (c)x= 20, in the as-cast and as-annealed state. Detailed scan of Coxalloys: (d)x= 5, (e)x= 10, (f)x= 20, respectively.

Microstructure of the as-cast Co5alloy. Representative BSE image showing the coarse grains (a) and elemental EDX maps showing distribution of Co (b), Cr (c), Fe (d), Mn (e), and Ni (f) in the area shown in (a).

Microstructure of the as-annealed Co5alloy at 850 °C for 48 h. Representative BSE image showing the coarse grains (a) and elemental EDX maps showing distribution of Co (b), Cr (c), Fe (d), Mn (e), and Ni (f) in the area shown in (a).
TEM image of the annealed Co5alloy. Inset shows the SADPs of the precipitate and the surrounding matrix.

Microstructure of the as-annealed Co10alloy at 850 °C for 48 h. Representative BSE image showing the coarse grains (a) and elemental EDX maps showing distribution of Co (b), Cr (c), Fe (d), Mn (e), and Ni (f) in the area shown in (a).

Microstructure of the as-annealed Co20alloy at 850 °C for 48 h. Representative BSE image showing the coarse grains (a) and elemental EDX maps showing distribution of Co (b), Cr (c), Fe (d), Mn (e), and Ni (f) in the area shown in (a).
Hardness evolution of Co5, Co10and Co20alloys with annealing time.
Tensile engineering stress-strain curves of Coxalloys in the as-cast state and as-annealed state at 850 °C for 48 h.
